##Why export from Trello?

- **Quickly extract** your Trello boards and cards for reporting, analysis, back-up, distribution, and transfer to other systems. 
- **Easily share information** with stakeholders who arenâ€™t on your Trello board.
- **Save time** by only exporting the information you need.

>"Board Export has cut my admin time by 50% when creating my reports from Trello"

##How can it help you?

Export nearly every Trello data point including boards, cards, comments, activity log, checklists, advanced lists, due dates and members. (NB - supported fields vary between export formats. For a full breakdown [click here](https://docs.adaptavist.com/be/latest/data-included-with-exports) )

To view an example Trello board click [here](http://bit.ly/3psC9to). And to view the sample export files click: [CSV](https://bit.ly/3xZtsLM), [Excel](https://bit.ly/3uFdC6T), [PDF](https://bit.ly/33wmRKD), [Image](https://bit.ly/2Sz1vKs)

##Pricing
All users start on a 14-day free trial of the Power-up (limited to 5 cards per export) and can upgrade anytime to one of the below plans.

# Pretty Print ðŸ–¨ï¸âœ¨ 
![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/hr.png)


> Sometimes it's handy to just have all your cards and their descriptions in one list. Maybe you want to print out your cards or export them to PDF.
> 
> With this Power-Up, you can choose which lists you want. The list, all its cards, their labels, and their descriptions will appear, fully formatted, ready to print or save.


## âš¡ï¸ Quick Start
![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/hr.png)

### 1. âœ¨ Click the *"Pretty Print"* board button.

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/step1.gif)

### 2. âš™ï¸ Adjust your preferences.

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/step2.gif)

### 3. ðŸ–¨ï¸ Print or ðŸ“ Export!

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/step3.gif)

## ðŸ’¡ Tips
![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/hr.png)

 You can use this Power-Up to export your board into a nicely formatted PDF document. Instead of choosing a printer, select *"Save as PDF"* in your print settings:

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/tip1.png)

ðŸ“„ The default margins are set to: 

>ðŸ’  **Paper Size:** A4
>
>ðŸ’  **Top and Bottom Margins:** 0.25in
>
>ðŸ’  **Left and Right Margins:** 0

If you wish to change this, you can do so in the print settings (in Chrome, check the *"More Settings"* option):

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/tip2.png)

If you don't like the amount of white space in your print preview, here are some things you can try:
    
>ðŸ’  Check or uncheck the box that says *"Start each list on a new page."*
>
>ðŸ’  Try printing out just 2-3 lists at a time. Sometimes this can help in grouping the lists more appropriately.

You can also disable the card colors to save printer ink! Just check the box that says *"Show card backgrounds"* and that formatting will disappear.

If you do want the colors to show up in print; however, make sure you double check your print settings and *turn on background graphics*:

![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/tip4.png)

## â“ Help
![](https://itsdani.me/images/pretty-print/hr.png)

If you need assistance, feel free to get in touch:

>ðŸ’  Email: [karendlyle@gmail.com](mailto:karendlyle@gmail.com)
>
>ðŸ’  [Github Repository](https://github.com/souperstition/pretty-print)
